caption: The food is regularly fresh and delightful, staff members hands over awesome service. I really like the cleanliness and vibes. Will come back again.

Didn’t expect great food, just expected it to be quick. It ended up being quick but inedible. The rice was just mush, and the chicken wasn’t cooked.  Save your money, plenty of better options.  P.S. if you paid in cash keep your receipt. Bringing the food back without eating it will not get you a refund. They’ll look at the mush, apologize, and offer you a voucher for more mush.
This place sure knows how to please their customers. Always with a very nice mindset. The food is reasonably priced, regularly yummy and neat.
Always great stoner food

This spot is the one I always prefer. I visit plenty of restaurants but to this restaurant I  constantly return again and again. The stuff is very amicable and the cooking they serve is so good. I would always prefer to have a good dinner in this place. I highly recommend this place.
Pretty good Panda location for the train station. They are pretty rushed, though, so you need to move fast.
Good food
I simply liked their dishes. I always get great service there. The place is well kept and the workers are always very nice. Keep up the good work.

The food is great. Variety of foods and free refills on the sodas.

Good food as always, I'm assuming at this point, but I have a suggestion that would be very helpful... When you provide carry-out, specifically at a train station, could you please put utensils in the bag. Because when you get on a train and realize that you didn't get utensils you can't go back. I'm now stuck on a train, with a warm container of food, but no civil way of eating it.
Fantastic food and service.

A fantastic place to grab quick Chinese food. The place is neat and staff very patient and friendly. This is one place that I couldn't resist whenever I pass through a nearby area. Food is always fresh and hot. You can see the staff cooking menu items in small portions so that all customers get served hot food. Price wise - you can have a quick lunch/dinner for 8-12 dollars per person which is not bad. Overall a good place to visit.
Just not that great
OK but greasy food in large portions reasonably priced. It's a food hall in a train station so there's not much in the way of atmosphere
Food not spicy nor tasty.
Good place for lunch. I recommend u to go there before 11:40am ish to avoid long line in weekdays.
Vegetables is fresh and food is good
Good amount of food for the price. Especially for the location.

If you have never had Chinese food before, you might like this place. I have been to other Panda Express but this one was the worst considering food at Panda Express is not that great to begin with. I went there because I had a Groupon. The amount of food I got was very little compared to what I paid for. The quality of the food wasn’t very good either and tasted too sweet and stale, even the condiments tasted odd. Service was fast though.
Chaw main for life !!!
Some great healthy options!
They don't give you enough meats to go with all the rice they give you

They are fast and efficient.  The food is always fresh.  I've eaten there a ton and my only gripes are the long lines at lunch which the staff is very pushy about getting through.  If you haven't seen the items you'll feel pressured to pick fast.  Also the online ordering system is not the best.  Lots of times they have to make it right there when you go for pick-up.  Doesn't take long just can be improves.  Two item meal with side is about $8.50 with tax

Huge Panda Express fan, I could eat at one everyday. This location was one of the worst I've been too in terms of food quality. Could've just been a fluke but the chicken and beef I had was not very good. Long lines, but they moved pretty quickly.
Kind staffs, delicious foods!
Great service & clean.  Never too long of a wait for any dish.
If you want Chinese food, don't go anywhere else!
Good food, quick service. Standard Panda Express.
Long, but rapid lines at lunch. Standard Food Court Chinese Food fare. Relatively wide selection of items however ensures that variety can be enjoyed if eating there more than once a week.
Bad Service.. I ordered Ku Pao Chicken and pepper Chicken Online and when I picked up the food and returned back. I barely see chicken in it. I wouldn't choose this location any more..
Great food. Reasonable prices.

Being situated in a prime spot within the downtown, this place has one advantage. Still I don't know why it   hadn't got very low stars. Yet I liked it. If you do like Chinese food and you are looking for lunch/dinner after work, I guess this is a good place. The other day I tried orange chicken, it was too sweet for me. This time I tried Kung Pao Chicken and Black Pepper Chicken with fried rice, they were also sweet, but a bit lesser. It was tasty no doubt. I can't complain about the crowd because I didn't face any, I was the only one ordering. They were almost closing, but they didn't seem annoyed that I was ordering at the last moment. They carried the food outside for me. That's a good point to note. I was happy, so 4 stars in the end is a good trade.
I've been here aruond 5 times, and each time was sub par.  The food seemed dry and overcooked.  The rice stuck together far too easily to enjoy the meal.  Beef was ok 2 times, but dry the other 3.

For a fast food Americanized Chinese spot Panda Express isn't bad, if you are in a mall. My problem with it being in the city is there are so many better options in the immediate area that its hard to justify spending money here.  That being said if you prefer your Chinese food totally Americanized over the real thing which you can get at a million places in a 1 mile area I always have to vote going with the Orange Chicken.  I've been at this specific location once (taken by a co-worker kicking and screaming!) and will give it full credit for being a clean environment with a friendly staff.  The food here really isn't bad for fast food by any stretch and at least you won't be feeling like you just ate a pound of grease with your food when you chow down.
Staff was nice, food was ok.
